The show is actually the story of a young man , leading an unhappy married life with a bad wife for the sake of happiness of his family ; a vicious woman who can do anything to satisfy her evil motives to gain money and power and a selfless girl who sacrifices her own love to solve all the problems in her lover 's married life .

The title may also point to the passing of an old order following the cataclysm of the First World War ; the supposed inadequacies of patriotism , the interest of some in atheism , feminism , socialism and pacifism , the changes to traditional married life , and not least the emergence of new styles of literary expression , are all treated in the work , bearing as they did directly on Graves ' life .

The unsentimental and frequently comic treatment of the banalities and intensities of the life of a British army officer in the First World War gave Graves fame , notoriety and financial security , but the book 's subject is also his family history , childhood , schooling and , immediately following the war , early married life ; all phases bearing witness to the `` particular mode of living and thinking '' that constitute a poetic sensibility .
Little does the couple realise what lies in wait for them in married life .
